            SortOrder = 1,
            AppRoutes = """["/dashboard"]""",
            Tags = """["dashboard","widgets","home"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Dashboard Overview\n\nThe Dashboard is your home screen — the first thing you see after logging in. It gives you an at-a-glance summary of your day: tasks due, jobs by stage, orders in progress, and planning cycle status. Everything is organized into cards you can drag around to match how you work.\n\n### Card-Based Layout\n\nThe Dashboard is a grid of cards. Each one shows a different piece of information. Drag a card to move it, and your layout is saved automatically — it looks the same next time you log in, even on another device. In edit mode you can add or remove cards.\n\n### Core Cards\n\n**Today's Tasks:** Shows your assigned jobs, with overdue ones at the top and highlighted so you know what needs attention first. Click any job to open its details.\n\n**Jobs by Stage:** A bar chart of how many jobs sit in each board stage, so you can see where work is piling up.\n\n**Open Orders:** A summary of open sales orders — the total count plus how many are Confirmed, In Production, and Partially Shipped. A quick read on your pipeline without leaving the dashboard.\n\n**Cycle Progress:** Shows how far along your current planning cycle is. You see how many entries are done out of the total, and a colored label warns you when the cycle is overdue.\n\n**End of Day:** A place to jot down your top 3 priorities for tomorrow. Type them and save; once saved, the card shows what you wrote with an Edit button.\n\n**Margin Summary:** Average margin percentage plus revenue, cost, and margin totals for recent jobs (only when Forge handles your accounting).\n\n### Getting Started Banner\n\nNew users see a Getting Started banner that tracks setup progress — creating your first job, adding a customer, setting up track types, and exploring reports. It disappears once you've done enough of these steps, and you can also close it yourself.\n\n### Other Cards\n\nThere are more cards to choose from: Team Load (how busy each person is), Deadlines (upcoming due dates), Activity (a recent activity feed), Action Items (follow-ups you can complete or dismiss), and Inventory Snapshot (part counts and low-stock alerts). Which cards you can use depends on what your install has turned on.\n\n### How It Loads\n\nThe Dashboard shows a brief loading screen while it pulls in everything at once. When it's ready, the whole dashboard appears together — no half-loaded cards or flickering.","sections":[]}"""
