            ContentJson = """{"passingScore":80,"questionsPerQuiz":8,"shuffleOptions":true,"showExplanationsAfterSubmit":true,"questions":[{"id":"db1","text":"You log in and see a brief loading screen before the Dashboard appears. Why does the Dashboard load this way?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The Dashboard is slow because it renders 3D graphics"},{"id":"b","text":"It pulls in all its information at once and shows the whole dashboard together when it's ready","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Each card loads on its own with its own spinner"},{"id":"d","text":"The loading screen is a bug — the Dashboard should appear instantly"}],"explanation":"The Dashboard gathers all its information at once and shows a brief loading screen. When everything is ready, the whole dashboard appears together — no half-loaded cards or flickering."},{"id":"db2","text":"You see a job highlighted in red in the Today's Tasks card. What does this mean?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The job has been flagged as high priority by a manager"},{"id":"b","text":"The job's due date has passed — it's overdue","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"The job is blocked by a hold and cannot proceed"},{"id":"d","text":"The job was recently assigned to you and hasn't been viewed yet"}],"explanation":"Jobs past their due date are shown in red in the Today's Tasks card so they stand out and get your attention first."},{"id":"db3","text":"You rearrange your Dashboard cards by dragging them to new positions. What happens to your layout?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"It resets to default when you refresh the page"},{"id":"b","text":"It's saved automatically and stays that way across sessions and devices","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"It's only saved in the current browser tab"},{"id":"d","text":"You need to click a Save Layout button to keep the changes"}],"explanation":"Card positions save automatically. Your layout comes back when you log in from any device — no Save button needed."},{"id":"db4","text":"The Cycle Progress card's label has turned red and reads 'Overdue'. What does this tell you?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The planning cycle has been paused by an admin"},{"id":"b","text":"Every entry in the cycle is now complete"},{"id":"c","text":"The cycle is past its end date — you're behind schedule with work still outstanding","isCorrect":true},{"id":"d","text":"The card failed to load and is showing an error"}],"explanation":"The Cycle Progress label normally counts down the days left in the cycle. Once the cycle passes its end date it turns red and reads 'Overdue' — a cue that you're behind schedule with work still outstanding."},{"id":"db5","text":"You want to write down your top 3 priorities for tomorrow from the Dashboard. How?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Go to the Planning page and add them to the next cycle"},{"id":"b","text":"Type them into the End of Day card and click Save","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"They're generated automatically — you can't enter them yourself"},{"id":"d","text":"You can only enter them from a job's details"}],"explanation":"The End of Day card is where you jot down your top 3 for tomorrow. Type them and click Save; the card then shows your note with an Edit button to change it later."},{"id":"db6","text":"You click a job in the Today's Tasks card. What happens?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The job's card is highlighted on the board"},{"id":"b","text":"The job's details open, showing subtasks, files, activity, and available actions","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"A small tooltip appears with the job title and due date"},{"id":"d","text":"You're taken to the Backlog page with that job selected"}],"explanation":"Clicking a job in Today's Tasks opens its full details, where you can see and manage subtasks, files, and activity history, and take actions like updating status."},{"id":"db7","text":"A new employee logs in and sees a 'Getting Started' banner on their Dashboard. When does this banner disappear?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"After 7 days, no matter what"},{"id":"b","text":"Only after every setup step shows a checkmark"},{"id":"c","text":"Once enough setup steps are done — like creating a job, adding a customer, and setting up track types — or when the employee closes it with the X","isCorrect":true},{"id":"d","text":"It never disappears — it turns into a regular card"}],"explanation":"The Getting Started banner tracks setup steps (creating your first job, adding a customer, setting up track types, receiving first stock, exploring reports — only the ones that apply to your install). It disappears once enough are done, and you can also close it yourself with the X."},{"id":"db8","text":"You glance at the Jobs by Stage card. What does the length of each bar represent?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"How long jobs have been sitting in that stage"},{"id":"b","text":"How many jobs are in that stage, sized against the busiest stage","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"The total dollar value of jobs in that stage"},{"id":"d","text":"How overdue the jobs in that stage are"}],"explanation":"Jobs by Stage draws one bar per board stage. The busiest stage has the longest bar and the others are sized against it. The exact count is shown next to each bar."},{"id":"db9","text":"The Inventory Snapshot card shows a low-stock count highlighted in an alert color. What is it telling you?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"That many parts are missing a description"},{"id":"b","text":"That some parts have dropped to or below their minimum stock level","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"That inventory counts haven't been reconciled this month"},{"id":"d","text":"That new stock has just been received"}],"explanation":"The Inventory Snapshot card shows the part count, total on hand, and a low-stock count. When parts fall to or below their minimum level, that number is highlighted and the affected parts are listed with their current versus minimum quantities."},{"id":"db10","text":"How are jobs ordered in the Today's Tasks card?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Alphabetically by job title"},{"id":"b","text":"Overdue first, then active, upcoming, and completed","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"By creation date — newest first"},{"id":"d","text":"Randomly each time the page loads"}],"explanation":"Today's Tasks lists jobs by status: overdue first so they get attention right away, then active, upcoming, and completed. It shows the top few and adds an alert at the top when any are past due."},{"id":"db11","text":"You want to see how many sales orders are currently in production. Where do you look on the Dashboard?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"The quick numbers at the top of the page"},{"id":"b","text":"The Open Orders card — it splits the total into Confirmed, In Production, and Partially Shipped","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"The Today's Tasks card — count the items yourself"},{"id":"d","text":"The Cycle Progress card — it splits things by stage"}],"explanation":"The Open Orders card shows the total open sales orders plus a split into Confirmed, In Production, and Partially Shipped. Look at the In Production number for your answer."},{"id":"db12","text":"The Action Items card lists a follow-up. What two quick actions can you take on it right from the card?","options":[{"id":"a","text":"Reassign it or change its priority"},{"id":"b","text":"Complete it (checkmark) or dismiss it (X)","isCorrect":true},{"id":"c","text":"Print it or export it to PDF"},{"id":"d","text":"Snooze it or escalate it to a manager"}],"explanation":"Each Action Items row has a checkmark to complete the follow-up and an X to dismiss it, so you can clear it without leaving the dashboard. When there's nothing left, the card shows a friendly empty message."}]}"""
