            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Reference,
            EstimatedMinutes = 4,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 90,
            AppRoutes = """["/dashboard"]""",
            Tags = """["dashboard","reference","advanced"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## The Dashboard Fits Whatever Screen You're On\n\nYour dashboard looks right whether you open it on a wide office monitor, a laptop, or a phone at the machine. On a big screen the cards sit side by side; on a narrow one they stack into a single column so you never have to scroll sideways or pinch to read. It adjusts on the fly, so if you shrink the window or collapse the sidebar, the cards re-flow to fit right away — nothing to set up. You rearrange or resize cards only while Customize (edit mode) is on; the rest of the day the layout is locked so you can't nudge a card out of place by accident.\n\n## Your Layout Follows You Everywhere\n\n**Set it once, get it everywhere.** However you arrange your cards is tied to you, not to the computer you're sitting at. Log in from the shop-floor terminal, your desk, or a laptop at home and you get the same dashboard you set up. It remembers every move, resize, add, and remove the moment you make it in edit mode — there's no Save button to forget. If you've experimented yourself into a mess, **Reset** (in edit mode) wipes your changes and brings back the standard set of cards, so you can always start clean.\n\n**Focus Mode is remembered on its own.** Your choice of Focus Mode is kept separately from your card layout. So you can leave Focus Mode on, and it stays on next time. If you live in Focus Mode all day, bookmark the page while it's on — that bookmark opens straight into Focus Mode every morning.\n\n**It stays current on its own.** Open the dashboard and it loads once, then keeps its numbers fresh in the background while you work — no need to reload the page to see the latest overdue count or new order. Leave the page and it stops working in the background, so it isn't churning away when you're off doing something else.\n\n## Let the Dashboard Become a Wall Display When You Step Away\n\nAmbient Mode turns the dashboard into a big, glanceable status board for a wall monitor. You can flip to it yourself, or set the dashboard to switch over on its own after you've been away from the keyboard for a while — handy for a screen the whole shop walks past.\n\n**It's off until you turn it on.** Auto-switching is something you opt into, and you pick how long to wait before it kicks in — anywhere from a minute to an hour. Any time you touch the keyboard, mouse, or screen counts as being there, so it only flips over during a real lull, never mid-task.\n\n**It won't interrupt real work.** The auto-switch holds off while you're editing your layout or already heads-down in Focus Mode, so it never yanks you out of what you're doing. And it's instant to leave — press Escape or click anywhere and you're back to the normal dashboard, right where you were. On the wall it keeps the clock and the headline numbers live, so a monitor across the shop never shows stale figures.\n\n## Every Nudge Action Items Can Give You\n\nAction Items is your follow-up list — the things worth doing before they turn into problems. It watches across the whole business and surfaces the ones that need a person, each with an icon so you can tell at a glance what it's about. Depending on your role and what your shop uses, you may see nudges for:\n\n- **A quote about to expire** — send it or re-quote before you lose the deal\n- **A stale lead** — nobody's followed up in a while\n- **An invoice past due** — time to chase payment\n- **A delivery at risk** — a shipment that may miss its date\n- **A cost overrun** — a job running over its estimate\n- **A certification about to expire** — renew before it lapses\n- **Maintenance due** — a machine or tool due for service\n- **A failed quality check** — an inspection that didn't pass\n- **A return received** — a customer sent something back\n- **A sales order confirmed** — an order ready to move into production\n- **Ready to ship** — a job cleared to go out the door\n- **Materials ready** — parts staged and waiting to run\n- **A shipment delivered** — an order that reached the customer\n\nThe most urgent follow-ups rise to the top, sorted by when they're due, and the card shows the handful that need attention first with a link to see the rest. Each nudge links straight to the record it's about, flags anything overdue, and gives you two one-click choices: a checkmark to mark it handled, or an X to dismiss it. Either clears it off your list right away. Clear them all and the card just says you're caught up.","sections":[]}"""
        });

        Log.Information("Seeded Dashboard training modules");
    }
